&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed &lt;/FONT&gt;– This is almost just like being evaluated however these items the development team is totally undecided if they want to implement or how to do so.&amp;nbsp; The Community Team plans to give updates on these types of items every 2 weeks, even if it’s just a “no change since the last update”&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Done&lt;/FONT&gt; – This means that the development team has implemented this item and it’s currently on live servers.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently on Test server&lt;/FONT&gt; – This means that the development team has implement this item and it’s currently on test server, watch for future updates for implementation on the live servers.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This one I need your help on &lt;/FONT&gt;– This means we don’t have enough information to make any type of decision on how to implement.&amp;nbsp; Threads will be started by me to get your feedback.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;No changes planned at this time&lt;/FONT&gt; – This means that the development team has decided at this time not to implement this item.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;Items that are marked done will be removed from the top 10 issues lists and you as a class will be able to replace those with new issues.&amp;nbsp; Watch for posts on this in the next week, your class correspondents will be helping SOE update your top 10 issues lists with these new items.&amp;nbsp; If your top issues list was less then 10 issues to begin with you will be able to add more issues.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;You as a class will have the option to replace items that are marked as “no changes planned at this time” with new items or leave them on the list.&amp;nbsp; Please understand that leaving them on the list does not mean that they will eventually be implemented however it does mean that the class as a whole still feels that these are valid issues and would like implementation eventually.&amp;nbsp; One thing to note, we will not be responding to requests as to why something is classified the way it is.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;This post will be locked and updated bi-weekly.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Gothic?? ?Century FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;&gt;--&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;1) Better Mitigation – &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;SPAN 1? **Zowie**?mso-tab-count:&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This is currently being evaluated&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;2) &lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; italic? mso-bidi-font-style: normal; **Zowie**?FONT-STYLE:&gt;Spell obsolescence – &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt;Heals&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt;: &lt;/U&gt;There is a ceiling against which the Paladin cannot go healing wise with the current design structure that f exceeded would make our heals as powerful as shaman or druid, which would be patently wrong. My only suggestion would be to give us very &amp;nbsp;large healing, extremely fast casting heals that have a bad mana to heal ratio.&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This is something that will improve in future expansions.)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt;Stuns&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt;:&lt;/U&gt; Stuns are at best, extremely useful and at works hideously deadly and bad to use. Stuns are perhaps the single most powerful tool in the Paladins arsenal and the defining spell line that combined with their tanknig makes them what they are.&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;This is something that will improve in future expansions.)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt;Lull&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt;:&lt;/U&gt; Disappears totally at level 55.&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;This is something that will improve in future expansions.)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt;Roots&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt;:&lt;/U&gt; Currently our highest level root works. Works pretty darn well. I could argue that I would like a longer duration on it but that would be more like than a critical need. The sole complaint is again, illogically or spuriously flagged unrootable mobs. Again another spell line that becomes disobviated by mob level and content design philosophy. It is the ONLY means of crowd control a paladin brings to a group or raid and it is again disobviate on a great many 'trash; type mobs with no real good reason I can see. Another case of the class losing core functionality with no balancing factor.&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;This is something that will improve in future expansions.)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt;Undead&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;&lt;U&gt; -&lt;/U&gt; Paladins are the 'most powerful class against the undead'. We have a good arsenal of abilities versus the undead. Sadly as you advance past level 60 the amount of undead in the game becomes almost laughable. Give us conent on which to utilize our toolset. Otherwise the tools are a waste of time and effort. Planes of power saw a dearth of undead in the expansion. Discord has almost NO undead whatsoever that I have seen from start through Ikkinz and I expect more of the same from Omens. Why give us a power focus and then give us NOTHING to utilize it on? An advantage is NOT an advantage if it is functioanlly useless. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;This is currently being evaluated)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;U&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; normal; bold? mso-bidi-font-weight: **Zowie**?FONT-WEIGHT:&gt;Pacification Spell Line&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;:&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/U&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt; Right now, as it stands, we cannot pacify lvl 55+ mobs. But, Shackles of Tunare allows us to still maintain the ability to pull, if in a somewhat different fashion.&amp;nbsp;It allows for single or double pull situations, and in MOST cases, that is sufficient. While getting the next level of this spell&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;3) Paladin Disciplines need a rework durations, usefulness etc…&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; auto?&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: Verdana; mso-fareast-font-family:&gt;&lt;SPAN Ignore? **Zowie**?mso-list:&gt;1.&lt;SPAN Roman?? New ?Times 7pt **Zowie**?FONT:&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:&gt;Resistant - Raises all of your resists by 10 for 5 minutes. This is very weak, and from what I read, no one ever uses it. I know I don't &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in list tab-stops: level1 mso-list: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; 0pt **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify; auto? .5in; lfo10; l8&gt;&lt;SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: Verdana; mso-fareast-font-family:&gt;&lt;SPAN Ignore? **Zowie**?mso-list:&gt;2.&lt;SPAN Roman?? New ?Times 7pt **Zowie**?FONT:&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:&gt;Fearless - Makes you 100% fear resistant for 11 seconds. Yep, I said that right, 11 seconds. Not only that, but it is totally superceeded by an AA that makes this discipline 100% useless. After getting the Fearless AA, this discipline is never ever used. &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in list tab-stops: level1 mso-list: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; 0pt **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify; auto? .5in; lfo10; l8&gt;&lt;SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: Verdana; mso-fareast-font-family:&gt;&lt;SPAN Ignore? **Zowie**?mso-list:&gt;3.&lt;SPAN Roman?? New ?Times 7pt **Zowie**?FONT:&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:&gt;Holyforge - Lasts for 2 minutes, and nakes it 3 times more likely to get a&amp;nbsp;crit, crippling blow or slay. The net effect of this is to raise our dps by 20% which brings us equal to a warrior in dps. Now this sucker really makes me mad. We are supposed to be the greatest force versus undead and we end up with a discipline that keeps us last or tied for last on dps versus undead. Very very unhappy with this discipline. &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in list tab-stops: level1 mso-list: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in; 0pt **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify; auto? .5in; lfo10; l8&gt;&lt;SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: Verdana; mso-fareast-font-family:&gt;&lt;SPAN Ignore? **Zowie**?mso-list:&gt;4.&lt;SPAN Roman?? New ?Times 7pt **Zowie**?FONT:&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:&gt;Sanctification - Makes us immune to most type of harmful spells for 10 seconds. Again &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: Verdana; 10.0pt? mso-bidi-font-size:&gt;10&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:&gt; seconds, and does not block unresistable spells. This is worse then useless. Not only do you never use this, how can you ever know when to use it and not blow it. The best use for this spell is during ldons when you break open a chest. That's it.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; auto?&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:&gt;None of these disciplines are usleful in any meaningful way today. We want ones that are. I'm not being a class rep here, these are toned down and shorter explanations of what the community thinks. Our one defensive discipline lasts for 10 seconds against only spells and our one offensive discipline lasts for 2 minutes versus only undead and does not raise our dps to the level of a warrior who is second to last on the dps scale, while we are supposed to be the undead fighters.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; auto?&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:&gt;A few other notes about Holyforge. It is the only discipline that requires you to get specific AA's to increase your chance of even getting a crit, cripple or slay. Paldins do not get crits till they buy an AA for critting. And Holyforge only gives you a three times chance of getting a crit, cripple or slay, and the&amp;nbsp;Fury of the Ages AA does not get factored into the equasion. So, while it does increase your chance for a crit or cripple it does not increase your chance while Holyforge is running. Why do we have a discipline that is linked to our AA's? This is all very frustrating.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; auto?&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: red; COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;4) &lt;SPAN italic? **Zowie**?mso-bidi-font-style:&gt;Utility in group and raids&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; italic? mso-bidi-font-style:&gt;&lt;SPAN 1? **Zowie**?mso-tab-count:&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;5) Using a shield needs to be more useful&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;Solution: tied to both Sks and Pallies. Change one of their discs to increase damage mitigation and/or prevent spell damage when used with shields in off hand for short durations. Also add or tweak current AAs to allow for more damage mitigation /ac only when equipping a shield in the off hand. Perhaps allow shields some way to block riposte damage&amp;nbsp;through an AA ability.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;6) Act of Valor aa ability:&amp;nbsp; Risk vs reward out of balance&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?&gt;7) &lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; normal; bold? mso-bidi-font-weight: **Zowie**?FONT-WEIGHT:&gt;Lay Hands&lt;/SPAN&gt; - PLEASE make it impossible to blow Lay Hands on a corpse or a mob!!!! And while you're at it, make it possible to see&amp;nbsp;how long before it's available like with an aability.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red;&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This has partially been fixed, the NPC part is still being looked into.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
